Hey again! I'm just sitting and relaxing at my laptop before going to my&nbsp;friend's house. We have plans of heading up to Thayer St.&nbsp;on the East Side of Providence and just chillin up there. I'm getting&nbsp;my lip pierced at Rockstar Body Piercing. I'm hoping that Jay can do it. He's done all my&nbsp;piercings. I know today's the day to get it&nbsp;done. I can feel it in my nuggets!&nbsp; 

Another thing is, according to my ex, I'm emotionally fucked up.&nbsp;No, I just didn't love her anymore. I felt it in my nuggs that it was time to move on. I don't think I'm emotionally closed up or fucked up. I&nbsp;had no problem loving my other ex or loving my friends and choosen family. That's okay, life goes&nbsp;on, doesn't it? 

Right now, I'm just keeping clear of being in any kind of relationship other than&nbsp;random dating. I'm&nbsp;interested in this young lady named Brittney. Thing is, I've never dated&nbsp;someone whose fem or bisexual. So this should be an interesting.&nbsp;I've liked her for&nbsp;awhile, but I don't want to start anything because we both recently got out of a long-term relationship.&nbsp; 

A couple of weeks ago, I went to the&nbsp;club with my sister and our best friend and my sister's mom (I call her ma also,&nbsp;even though she's not), I have to say, it was&nbsp;an interesting night since I took&nbsp;3 straight women, 2 of whom&nbsp;never been to a&nbsp;club at all, to&nbsp;Dyke Night&nbsp;at&nbsp;Club Energy.&nbsp;After getting some what shitfaced,&nbsp;we all went to IHop at&nbsp;2 am and enjoyed a nice breakfast. I never knew hashbrowns could taste so&nbsp;good after so many beers and shots.&nbsp; 

Another interesting thing,&nbsp;on Easter Sunday while I was at work, there was a stabbing in the apartment building across the parking lot from&nbsp;me. I have to say, it's quite spooky. In the neighborhood&nbsp;I live in, the worst that has ever happened here are&nbsp;random drug busts. But what can you do? Violence is everywhere, so matter where you go. 

To end this quickly, I have to say this.....Damn, is it just me, or is the taste of freedom really this sweet and delicious? Like a mango smoothie.

So, it's been some time since I last posted. I've decided that I need ideas of what I want to write. Give me some topic ideas. Like....what's something that bothered you today? Like, racism, sexism, homophobia.&nbsp;

I'm sitting here finishing my veggie soup (which I added some Italian bread and garlic hummus to it. YUM!!), finishing up my last smoke, and watching a repeat of the L Word.&nbsp;

I'm bored. Really, when I'm watching reruns of the L Word and WISHING I could hear the coyotes yelp.

Btw, gender sucks. Go f*ck it.

So, for those of u who don't know, I have to repeat my senior year because my guidence counsler didn't bother telling me till the last minute that (litterly a few weeks before&nbsp;graduation of 07) that I needed 3 credits to graduate. Well, it was way too late for me to do classes at CCRI, so now I'm repeating my senior year of high school. It's like...WTF. Pisses me off.&nbsp;

On top of that, I start my new job at Shaws in East Providence tomorrow. I'm only going to be making $7.55 an hour. Minimun wage in RI is $7.40. So...15 cents more...grrr and I'm only working part time.&nbsp;I'm seriously hoping I can get a pay raise soon. Like..to&nbsp;$8 bucks.&nbsp;Yeah, wishfull thinking, I know. It'll cost me a&nbsp;little over an hours pay to&nbsp;buy a pay of cloves.&nbsp;

I know! I KNOW! I SHOULD QUIT.&nbsp;My girlfriend already got on my case about my "chain smoking." I'm not a "chain smoker." I just...smoke...a lot. Like...a pack in two days. Well, I had 14 or 15 yesterday....I still have almost a whole pack of Pall Mall to finish once I've finish my Cloves. Damnit. I should cut back. I already cut back a little on drinking...I use to get drunk 3 or 4 times a week. Now it's like...2&nbsp;times a week. Hmmm...

BE GLAD NATALIE! I'M CUTTING BACK.

So, right now I'm babysitting. The boys are upstairs playing for awhile. We just got done with a very messy art project. Glitter everywhere. Even on my boots. MY BITCH BOOTS. ::cires::&nbsp;

Anyway. Getting off at 2p est. Can't wait. Love the boys, but I'm really tired. I only have a few hours of sleep. Fall asleep while on the phone with my lady. Haha. She called me stubborn.&nbsp;

Yeah. What else is going down? Oi, saw my friend Rooster yesterday. Was exciting. I love her.

Hey, so..some interesting things are going down as usual. I'm heading to a keg party this Friday and hopefully my friend Alisha will come with me. On top of that, I might be going on a date with my ex Ashley. Idno yet.&nbsp;

I've been going to Club Energy a lot lately. I stopped going for awhile, but now I am....again. There's this chick named Shana that I'm really interested in hooking up with. But I fucking hate her boyfriend. Maybe things will change. I just wanna fuck her.&nbsp;

Hmmm....what else? Oi, there's this really hot Indian chick that works at Purfume Bazaar in the Providence Place Mall. I couldn't help but stare at her. Sry Nat.&nbsp;

Fuck! What else? Damn...I might go to Chicago in Feburary depending if things work out with Nat and if I have the money.&nbsp;

I'm seeing my ex tomorrow. The senisible part of me knows that seeing her will make me upset and cry. But the unreasonable part of me wants to see her really badly.

So, a lotta things are going down.&nbsp;

I've been going to Boston alot. I feel right there. It's like it's my calling. I hope I can live there in the next three years.

I have a new lady in my life. Her name's Nat. She's from Chicago, Ill. We have an open relationship. Pretty. She's gonna be coming down in about a month to visit .Can't wait.

What else is going down? Hmm...

I start my new job at Shaws on either Tuesday or Wednesday. Pretty exciting. Gonna be bagging food and collecting carts. Eh. A job is job. Money in the bank and cigs in my pocket. I might plan a trip to Chicago in Feb. if I have the money.&nbsp;

Soo...that's about it...K.D LANG'S MY WIFE. haha. I wish.

Well, I finally decided to create a new LJ. Things have been pretty crazy lately.&nbsp;

In the past 4 months, I've broken up with a girl that I've come to realize, that I loved.

I've been kicked out of my mom's place...allowed back...only to be kicked out again. Well, I'm living with my mom again....for now.

I have a second job interview at Shaws in my hometown. I can't continue on without a job. I won't lie.....I've been a complete typical job-less and money-less punk whom spends her last few dollars on a pack of smokes and some beer.&nbsp;

I'm tired of sleeping under bridges or at a friend's place when my mom kicks me out. I'm tired of wearing the same&nbsp;few pairs of pants over and over. My boots and sneakers need duct tape. My big black boots are slowly&nbsp; falling apart and I have holes on the bottom of my sneaks.&nbsp;

I most def need to hit up some garage sales before fall really kicks in and it gets way too cold.&nbsp;

This is only a short version of what's happening in my life. So yeah, I'll keep y'all posted.
